    .col-md-6
      #section-head
        %h5 Applications
      %br
      #section-body
        Using an approach based on the 
        %b optimization of the power 
        generated by catabolic processes allows one to account for 
        %b dynamic 
        environmental conditions (e.g., variability of temperature, pH, ionic strength, activities of redox active species). The method can be applied to simulate the redox stratification observed in 
        %b early diagenesis 
        and other 
        %b energy-limited environments, 
        such as oligotrophic aquifers, where energy substrates are in low abundance.
